summary: My thoughts on the TS7 theories!!!
body:
My thoughts on the TS7 theories!!!

There’s so much theories on tumblr (alone) that I don’t even know where and what to believe in.

So many Dates that makes sense. Collaborations that also makes sense and those aren’t just a guess, those are theories supported by facts.

Based on the theories I have read.


There are something going on the 13th of May and July.


Some theories indicate that she will collab with

-Selena Gomez

-Paul Klein

-Drake

-Dixie Chicks

-Arianna Grande

And so many more. Like what I said, these theories are supported by clues and eastereggs.


The craziest Theory I have read is.


THERE ARE TWO SETS OF SONGS!!


And I read about the concept “ME! And YOU!” Since the merch has a No.1 printed on it.

She also told us in the interview with EW that there are more songs in this album compared to her previous albums.


One Swiftie theorize that maybe the reason why she released ME! On the 26th of april is because there were 26 songs, 13 on each side.


That just about it. For now. More crazy theories are about to come up.Toodles!



@taylorswift @taylorswiftstyle @taylor-swiftfacts @taylornation

summary: FELINE FRIENDLY:  T-Swift loves cats (duh). Now she’s playing one in the big-screen version of Andrew Lloyd Webber’s musical. ...
body:
FELINE FRIENDLY:  T-Swift loves cats (duh). Now she’s playing one in the big-screen version of Andrew Lloyd Webber’s musical.


Entertainment Weekly (May 17th 2019 issue)

When director Tom Hooper first approached Swift about playing Bornbalurina in the film Cats, she had more than a few questions. 

“Obviously, I loved the show, I loved the music, and one of the things that made Cats so special when it came out in the ‘80s was that it was presented in a way people hadn’t seen before,” she says. 

“[But] what about this is going to give people that same awe factor [that] we’re seeing something completely original? I was like, ‘Are we gonna be in the Lycra catsuits with fur glued to us? Like, what are we talking about here?”

So Hooper showed Swift - who had small roles in the films Valentine’s Day and The Giver - a demo of what to expect. “They add digital fur to us. They’re completely human performances. It’s not animated. And it’s not motion capture. It’s somehow this new way that hasn’t been done before. And they’re giving us a tail that moves naturally and ears and whiskers. It was one of the coolest things I’ve seen.”

Of course, Swift went into the experience with all the zeal you’d expect from a dedicated cat mom. “I just fully committed and threw myself into the process and had the most fun. We had this thing called ‘cat school’ that was a class where you could learn about how to create the motions of cats, how to think like they think, how to sense things the way that they do, carry yourself the way a cat would. I learned a lot.”

summary: The last movie that had a major impact on Swift was the acclaimed 2018 documentary on Fred Rogers and his daytime...
text: The last movie that had a major impact on Swift was the acclaimed 2018 documentary on Fred Rogers and his daytime public-television show. “I was watching this movie sitting in bed bawling; all of a sudden, society decided that Mister Rogers had poisoned the youth of America by telling them each that they’re special,” says Swift, who watched Mister Rogers’ Neighborhood every day after school as a kid. “I was so upset because my mom raised me with [his] mindset: You’re special, everyone’s special, everyone’s an individual and deserves to have a beautiful, happy life and do what they love.” After the film, the singer-songwriter called her mom in tears. “She’s like, ‘Are you okay? Have you been in an accident?” recalls Swift, laughing. “I’m like, [mock cry-shouting] ‘He was just trying to do a good thing!” She adds that the things she learned on the program continue to resonate in her own life. “I try to tell fans: ‘You’re special. You actually are. You’re not replaceable, you’re not worthless.”
source: Taylor Swift about Mister Rogers and his mindset she still lives by - EW (May 17th 2019 issue)

summary: The Taylor Swift button cheat sheet (EW, May 17th 2019 issue) 1. SELENA GOMEZ. One of Taylor’s best friends (and one of the few...
caption:
The Taylor Swift button cheat sheet (EW, May 17th 2019 issue)

1. SELENA GOMEZ. One of Taylor’s best friends (and one of the few people who’s heard the new record).
2. DIXIE CHICKS. Swift is a huge fan of the trio: “They make interesting music in an unapologetically feminine way.”
3. CATS. Swift is playing Bombalurina in the big-screen adaptation.
4. CALM. “Je suis calme!” A.k.a. what Swift shouts in the music video for her new single, “ME!”
5. FRIENDS. Friends is a major staple in Swift world. Her favorite quote from the show? “Pivot!’ I take it as career advice.”
6. CATS. Not to be confused with the musical, Swift is mom to three cats: Olivia Benson, Meredith Grey, and Benjamin Button.
7. TROYE SIVAN. Swift is a big admirer of the Australian pop star, bringing him out to sing “My My My!” on the Reputation Tour.
8. GREY’S ANATOMY. Swift’s go-to Grey’s Anatomy quote: “So do it. Decide. Is this the life you want to live? Is this the person you want to love? Is this the best you can be?”
9. TRACK 5. A nod to the Swifties’ fan theory that the most emotional song on each of her albums is placed at track 5.
10. DRAKE. The pop star calls Drake one of her favorite lyricists.
11. FAITH HILL. One of Swift’s favorite singers.
12. MISTER ROGERS. Swift watched Mister Rogers’ Neighborhood every day after school.
13. LAW & ORDER: SPECIAL VICTIMS UNIT. Swift is a major Law & Order buff. The two-tone chime is also one of her favorite sounds.
14. PASTEL COLORS. The color palette, which she began using on Instagram in February, represents a brand-new era.
15. GAME OF THRONES. So if Swift had a Game of Thrones dragon, what would she name it? “Villanelle”.
16. AWESOME. A nod to the line she sings in “ME!”: “You can’t spell awesome without me.”
